00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:05.739
Good afternoon, everyone.

1
00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:08.249
Today's lesson is focused
on exploring the position

2
00:00:08.260 --> 00:00:10.439
of the tongue and
exactly how it works.

3
00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:13.208
This is very important for
your health, because if

4
00:00:13.219 --> 00:00:15.728
the tongue is positioned
incorrectly within the oral

5
00:00:15.739 --> 00:00:18.768
cavity, whether it is too
weak or too strong, it will

6
00:00:18.779 --> 00:00:20.139
press against the teeth.

7
00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:23.807
This pressure can eventually
change your dental bite,

8
00:00:23.819 --> 00:00:27.879
the alignment of the head,
and your overall posture.

9
00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:32.468
When positioned correctly,
the tongue should be situated

10
00:00:32.479 --> 00:00:33.959
right in this specific area.

11
00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:37.548
That is to say, it should be
pressed completely and firmly

12
00:00:37.559 --> 00:00:40.439
against the hard palate at
the very top of the mouth.

13
00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:43.249
However, it can often happen
that when a child breathes

14
00:00:43.260 --> 00:00:45.408
primarily through their
mouth, the tongue naturally

15
00:00:45.419 --> 00:00:47.588
drops down, and because
of this constant

16
00:00:47.599 --> 00:00:50.959
position, it eventually
becomes quite tense.

17
00:00:51.020 --> 00:00:54.239
Next, the jaw and neck muscles
will also become tense.

18
00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:56.229
Consequently, as a
result, we can end up

19
00:00:56.240 --> 00:00:59.919
with scoliosis, which is
something we want to avoid.

20
00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:03.819
So we teach young children
from a very early age.

21
00:01:05.340 --> 00:01:08.328
We teach them to place their
tongue upwards, finding the

22
00:01:08.339 --> 00:01:11.148
little ridges and bumps at
the very top of the mouth,

23
00:01:11.159 --> 00:01:14.288
and basically, we work to
strengthen the tongue muscles

24
00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:17.308
so that the child develops
correct pronunciation, very

25
00:01:17.319 --> 00:01:20.228
clear speech, and healthy,
good swallowing habits

26
00:01:20.239 --> 00:01:21.739
for their daily life.

27
00:01:21.760 --> 00:01:24.627
Because sometimes swallowing
is disrupted due to the

28
00:01:24.639 --> 00:01:28.588
position of the tongue, and
because of this, the muscles

29
00:01:28.599 --> 00:01:32.499
of the larynx and neck
will become tense.

